overview: The user initiated a request for a comprehensive review of their sleep
  questionnaire application, aiming to ensure all acceptance criteria from the
  Statement of Work and detailed specification were met. The agent performed an
  initial assessment, identifying several critical gaps and missing features.
  Subsequently, the agent proceeded to implement these identified items in an
  iterative manner. Key implementations included adding a 1-10 severity scale
  for tiredness with associated safety warnings, integrating detection logic for
  COMISA (Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome,
  incorporating placeholder outbound links to various sleep and mental health
  resources, and implementing a weighted scoring system for Excessive Daytime
  Sleepiness. Furthermore, the CSV export functionality was significantly
  expanded to include all questionnaire response data, and new questions for
  pain severity and chronic fatigue screening were added. The approach involved
  modifying existing types, validation schemas, and UI components (both web and
  PDF report generation) to integrate the new features and logic.
